<paragraph blockId="2.[136,788,1314,1946]" lastBlockId="2.[824,1476,1314,1946]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicName box="[174,318,1794,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eleagnos">
<emphasis box="[174,318,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Salix eleagnos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the central-southeastern 
<collectorName pageId="2" pageNumber="341">European</collectorName>
chorotype (
<bibRefCitation author="JALAS &amp; SUOMINEN" box="[321,603,1825,1850]" firstAuthor="JALAS" journalOrPublisher="Helsinki" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" refId="ref2888" refString="JALAS, J. &amp; J. SUOMINEN (1976). Atlas Florae Europaeae. 3. Salicaceae to Balanophoraceae. Helsinki." title="Atlas Florae Europaeae. 3. Salicaceae to Balanophoraceae" type="book" year="1976">JALAS &amp; SUOMINEN, 1976</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[622,650,1826,1849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Its</collectorName>
intraspecific variability is restricted to two subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scop. subsp. eleagnos" authorityYear="1772" box="[599,786,1858,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="eleagnos" subSpecies="eleagnos">
<emphasis box="[599,620,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">S.</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[702,786,1858,1882]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">eleagnos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cariot &amp; St.-Lag.) Rech." box="[183,692,1890,1914]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[183,204,1890,1913]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">S.</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[281,401,1890,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">angustifolia</emphasis>
(
<collectorName box="[415,487,1890,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Cariot</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[524,554,1890,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">St.</collectorName>
- 
<collectorName box="[562,615,1890,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Lag.</collectorName>
) 
<collectorName box="[631,692,1890,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Rech.</collectorName>
</taxonomicName>
f., based on leaf morphology (shape, ratio length/width and 
<typeStatus box="[709,756,1922,1946]" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">type</typeStatus>
of leaf margin). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:038187AD3A6EF632FC99FE871157FBE7:8EF760603A6DF633FC71FA93168EFA93" box="[969,1010,1314,1338]" country="Italy" name="The" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">The</location>
nominal subspecies seems by far the most dominant one in 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1054,1346,1370]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PIGNATTI" box="[1070,1240,1346,1370]" firstAuthor="PIGNATTI" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" refId="ref3005" refString="PIGNATTI, S. (1982). Fl. Italia vol. 1. Bologna." type="book" year="1982">PIGNATTI, 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="MARTINI &amp; PAIERO" firstAuthor="MARTINI" journalOrPublisher="Trieste" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" refId="ref2931" refString="MARTINI, F. &amp; P. PAIERO (1988). I salici d'Italia. Trieste." title="I salici d'Italia" type="book" year="1988">MARTINI &amp; PAIERO, 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[824,1476,1314,1946]" lastBlockId="3.[801,1453,279,1103]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="342" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">
<taxonomicName box="[862,1049,1410,1434]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[862,1049,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Salix crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described by 
<bibRefCitation author="BERTOLONI" box="[1207,1415,1410,1434]" firstAuthor="BERTOLONI" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" pagination="76" refId="ref2200" refString="BERTOLONI, A. (1813). Salix crataegifolia. J. Bot. Appl. (Desvaux) 2: 76." type="journal article" year="1813">BERTOLONI (1813)</bibRefCitation>
, represents one of the most interesting willow species in Europe. The arcuate-pendant posture of the catkins, always observable in the males while in the females noticeable only until flowering, represents an ancestral character. Moreover, the morphology of the vascular bundles of the leaves, the small size of the pollen grains and low chromosome number are typical characters of this palaeoendemic species, phytogeographically isolated (
<bibRefCitation author="BECHI" box="[979,1175,1665,1690]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="BECHI" journalOrPublisher="Webbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" pagination="31 - 37" part="51" refId="ref2168" refString="BECHI, N., G. CORSI &amp; F. GARBARI (1996). Indagini biosistematiche sulla flora apuana. IV contributo. Webbia 51: 31 - 37." title="Indagini biosistematiche sulla flora apuana. IV contributo" type="journal article" year="1996">BECHI et al., 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="GARBARI" box="[1191,1419,1666,1690]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="GARBARI" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" pagination="177 - 204" refId="ref2336" refString="GARBARI, F., G. BEDINI, M. ANSALDI &amp; D. MARCHETTI (2007). Fitogeografia apuana. Aggiornamenti biosistematici, tassonomici e corologici sulle Spermatophyta endemiche, relitte e critiche. Biogeographia 28: 177 - 204." type="journal article" year="2007">GARBARI et al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and with a limited individual variability. For these same reasons 
<bibRefCitation author="SKVORTSOV" box="[824,1022,1730,1754]" firstAuthor="SKVORTSOV" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" refId="ref3080" refString="SKVORTSOV, A. K. (1999). Willows of Russia and adjacent countries. Taxonomical and Geographical Revision. University of Joensuu Report series 39, Finland." type="book" year="1999">SKVORTSOV (1999)</bibRefCitation>
hypothesizes a link between several species of the Chinese Himalaya (
<taxonomicName authority="Anderss." authorityName="Anderss." box="[1111,1356,1762,1786]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sikkimensis">
<emphasis box="[1111,1250,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">S. sikkimensis</emphasis>
Anderss.,
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Anderss." authorityName="Anderss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="daltoniana">
S. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">daltoniana</emphasis>
Anderss.
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="C. K. Schneider" box="[1034,1309,1794,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ernesti">
<emphasis box="[1034,1130,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">S. ernesti</emphasis>
C.K. Schneider
</taxonomicName>
from Sichuan. 
<taxonomicName box="[824,1018,1826,1850]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[824,1018,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">Salix crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a steno-endemic chasmophyte of the Apuan Alps, with a distribution area of only 
<quantity box="[1351,1460,1857,1882]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.616" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" unit="km" value="261.6">261.6 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="right" box="[1461,1469,1857,1871]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="341">2</superScript>
, which has convinced 
<bibRefCitation author="ROMA-MARZIO" box="[1052,1356,1889,1914]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="ROMA-MARZIO" pageId="2" pageNumber="341" pagination="205 - 211" refId="ref3022" refString="ROMA-MARZIO, F., A. CARTA, A. DI SACCO, L. PERUZZI &amp; G. BEDINI (2015). Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare endemica di Toscana ed aree contermini. 8. Salix crataegifolia (Salicaceae). Inform. Bot. Ital. 47: 205 - 211." type="journal article" year="2015">ROMA-MARZIO et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
to propose its inclusion among the “Near Threatened” [NT] species. Considering the above discussed features and the absence of other hybrid forms with 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1271,311,335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[1114,1271,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a parent, the discovery of 
<emphasis box="[933,946,343,366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S</emphasis>
. × 
<emphasis box="[970,1071,343,367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">marchettii</emphasis>
has generated considerable surprise. Hence, among all 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1061,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1061,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hybrids, 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Merli &amp; F. Mart." box="[1164,1312,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xmarchettii">
<emphasis box="[1164,1177,375,398]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S</emphasis>
. × 
<emphasis box="[1205,1312,375,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">marchettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a unique case because it is the result of a cross with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore an endemic nothospecies of the Apuan Alps. From an ecological point of view, it behaves as a genuine gravel species like 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1094,503,527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eleagnos">
<emphasis box="[991,1094,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. eleagnos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1313,503,527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[1169,1313,503,527]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
prefers rocks (limestone and metamorphic) and is rarely growing on gravels (
<bibRefCitation author="ROMA-MARZIO" box="[810,1114,567,591]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="ROMA-MARZIO" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" pagination="205 - 211" refId="ref3022" refString="ROMA-MARZIO, F., A. CARTA, A. DI SACCO, L. PERUZZI &amp; G. BEDINI (2015). Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare endemica di Toscana ed aree contermini. 8. Salix crataegifolia (Salicaceae). Inform. Bot. Ital. 47: 205 - 211." type="journal article" year="2015">ROMA-MARZIO et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Merli &amp; F. Mart." box="[1133,1313,567,591]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xmarchettii">
<emphasis box="[1133,1187,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">Salix</emphasis>
× 
<emphasis box="[1208,1313,567,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">marchettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known so far from a single population on the northwestern slope of M. Pelato, where, however, it is fairly widespread on the road side gravel and on the underlying rocky slope, together with 
<taxonomicName box="[801,955,695,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[801,955,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(abundant), 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. eleagnos" authorityName="Scop. subsp. eleagnos" authorityYear="1772" box="[1099,1375,695,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="eleagnos" subSpecies="eleagnos">
<emphasis box="[1099,1210,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. eleagnos</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1291,1375,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">eleagnos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apennina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. apennina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(more rare), 
<taxonomicName box="[1045,1166,727,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis box="[1045,1166,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1315,727,751]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caprea">
<emphasis box="[1223,1315,727,751]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. caprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both occasional). According to the local distribution of the two parents as reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="FERRARINI &amp; MARCHETTI" box="[956,1322,791,815]" firstAuthor="FERRARINI" journalOrPublisher="Accad. Lunigianese Sci. G. Capellini. Studi e Documenti di Lunigiana" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" part="13" refId="ref2259" refString="FERRARINI, E. &amp; D. MARCHETTI (1994). Prodromo alla flora della Regione Apuana. Parte prima (Lycopodiaceae - Leguminosae). Accad. Lunigianese Sci. G. Capellini. Studi e Documenti di Lunigiana 13." title="Prodromo alla flora della Regione Apuana. Parte prima (Lycopodiaceae - Leguminosae)" type="journal volume" year="1994">FERRARINI &amp; MARCHETTI (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="ROMA-MARZIO, F. &amp; A. CARTA &amp; A. DI SACCO &amp; L. PERUZZI &amp; G. BEDINI" journalOrPublisher="Inform. Bot. Ital." pageId="3" pageNumber="342" pagination="205 - 211" part="47" refId="ref3022" refString="ROMA-MARZIO, F., A. CARTA, A. DI SACCO, L. PERUZZI &amp; G. BEDINI (2015). Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare endemica di Toscana ed aree contermini. 8. Salix crataegifolia (Salicaceae). Inform. Bot. Ital. 47: 205 - 211." title="Contributo alla conoscenza della flora vascolare endemica di Toscana ed aree contermini. 8. Salix crataegifolia (Salicaceae)" type="journal article" year="2015">ROMA-MARZIO et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, it can be hypothesized that 
<emphasis box="[1324,1337,823,846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S</emphasis>
. × 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">marchettii</emphasis>
could be sought with success at least where the parents are most common: for instance, in the Lunigiana area of the Apuan Alps (province of Massa-Carrara) and in the upper and middle valley of the river Serchio (Prov. Lucca). Finally, the discovery of 
<taxonomicName authority="M. Merli &amp; F. Mart." box="[974,1114,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xmarchettii">
<emphasis box="[974,987,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S</emphasis>
. × 
<emphasis box="[1012,1114,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">marchettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sheds new light on the capacity of hybridization of 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1162,1015,1039]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crataegifolia">
<emphasis box="[1012,1162,1015,1039]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. crataegifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and careful research could well lead to the identification of new hybrid forms, i.e. with 
<taxonomicName box="[801,891,1079,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caprea">
<emphasis box="[801,891,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. caprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1060,1079,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="342" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis box="[943,1060,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="342">S. purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
